ning the refactored program.' | [OUTPUT CONTRACT] EXACTLY 4 challenges. Structure MUST be: 1. Tech Lead Intro Email 2. Challenges. Each MUST follow EXACTLY: '#### Challenge [N]️⃣: [Short specific description]' followed by Brief explanation BEFORE code (what the code does), then '💩 Dirty Code:' followed by a Single code block (functional but messy and poorly written), then '💻 Program Output:' (code block, KEEP SAME FORMAT). 3. No final summary section | [REVIEW INTENT RULE] The user is expected to review, identify issues, and refactor the code to production-level quality | [CODE CONSTRAINTS] Each challenge MUST include: - Internal data OR dataset usage - At least 1 print statement - MUST be between 5–15 lines of EXECUTABLE code (STRICT: Do NOT count blank lines towards this limit, allow messy spacing) - NO classes - Single logical flow - Code MUST run correctly BUT be poorly structured, inconsistent, or inefficient | [FUNCTION RULE] Do NOT use functions unless absolutely required by the concept. Use linear scripts. | [CODE QUALITY RULE] Code MUST be executable and correct BUT intentionally messy, inconsistent, or suboptimal | [DIRTY CODE RULE] Code MUST: - Use very poor and inconsistent variable naming (e.g., x, tmp, a1, thing, data2) - Mix naming styles randomly across challenges - Have inconsistent formatting and spacing - Include redundant variables and unnecessary reassignment - Repeat conversions or operations unnecessarily - Use suboptimal or overly verbose logic - Include occasional compact one-liners mixed with overly expanded logic - Still be logically correct and runnable - NOT include ANY comments | [STYLE INCONSISTENCY RULE] Each challenge should feel like it was written at a different time with different formatting styles | [FILE HANDLING RULE] Use correct loaders and enforce encoding='utf-8' and newline='' when applicable | [DATA TYPE RULE] Explicit casting required before calculations | [DATA ROBUSTNESS RULE] Handle missing, malformed, or inconsistent 